7. Authorization Attack Engine ⚔️

This module performs attacks automatically.

1. IDOR Testing

Modify IDs automatically:

/api/user/101
/api/user/102
/api/user/103

Compare responses.

2. Horizontal Privilege Escalation

Use same session but change user ID.

Example:

/api/orders?user_id=200
3. Vertical Privilege Escalation

Normal user trying admin endpoints:

/admin
/admin/settings
/admin/users
4. Role Manipulation

Modify parameters:

role=user → admin
is_admin=false → true
5. Token Manipulation

Modify JWT payload:

role:user → role:admin
6. HTTP Method Manipulation

Try:

GET
POST
PUT
DELETE
PATCH

Example:

DELETE /api/user/101
8. Smart Response Analyzer 🧠

Your tool must detect vulnerabilities automatically.

Detection techniques:

Response Code Analysis
401 unauthorized
403 forbidden
200 success

If:

normal user → admin endpoint → 200

Then vulnerability.

Response Length Comparison

Example:

response1 = 1200 bytes
response2 = 1200 bytes

Possible IDOR.

Data Pattern Detection

Look for:

email
username
account data
orders
9. Automatic Vulnerability Detection 🚨

Example detection logic.

IDOR Logic
if parameter_changed
and response_data_different_user
then IDOR vulnerability
Admin Bypass Logic
if normal_user_access_admin_endpoint
and response_code == 200
then privilege escalation
Token Manipulation Logic
if modified_token_grants_admin_access
then broken authentication
